{
  "video_id": "mKklMK027HM",
  "title": "Chapter 7",
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 467.0,
      "end_time": 1834.0,
      "text": ">> All right, in the next few weeks,"
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 1834.0,
      "end_time": 5700.0,
      "text": "we&#39;re gonna talk about contracts."
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 5700.0,
      "end_time": 8000.0,
      "text": "In chapter 7, we&#39;re gonna focus in on"
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 8000.0,
      "end_time": 9500.0,
      "text": "the first two elements of contracts--"
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 9500.0,
      "end_time": 13400.0,
      "text": "agreement and consideration."
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 13400.0,
      "end_time": 16266.0,
      "text": "Contract law is based on the common law,"
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 16265.0,
      "end_time": 18433.0,
      "text": "which we&#39;ve talked about already,"
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 18433.0,
      "end_time": 21500.0,
      "text": "except for contracts for the sale of goods,"
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 21500.0,
      "end_time": 24233.0,
      "text": "which are governed by statutory law,"
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 24233.0,
      "end_time": 28533.0,
      "text": "specifically the Uniform Commercial Code, or the UCC."
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 28533.0,
      "end_time": 30600.0,
      "text": "The idea is that they would provide stability"
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 30600.0,
      "end_time": 32700.0,
      "text": "and predictability for commerce."
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 34767.0,
      "end_time": 37867.0,
      "text": "Contract is a promise or set of promises for a breach"
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 37867.0,
      "end_time": 39867.0,
      "text": "to which the law provides a remedy,"
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 39867.0,
      "end_time": 41867.0,
      "text": "or the performance of which the law"
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 41867.0,
      "end_time": 44000.0,
      "text": "in some way recognizes as a duty."
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 46100.0,
      "end_time": 47567.0,
      "text": "The Objective Theory of Contracts"
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 47567.0,
      "end_time": 50834.0,
      "text": "is applied by the court,"
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 50834.0,
      "end_time": 53100.0,
      "text": "and it looks to the circumstances"
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 53100.0,
      "end_time": 55100.0,
      "text": "to determine the intent of the parties."
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 55100.0,
      "end_time": 58867.0,
      "text": "Rather, it looks at the objective facts,"
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 58867.0,
      "end_time": 60934.0,
      "text": "including what a party may have said"
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 60934.0,
      "end_time": 62132.0,
      "text": "when entering into the contract,"
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 62133.0,
      "end_time": 65367.0,
      "text": "how the party acted or appeared,"
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 65367.00000000001,
      "end_time": 69433.0,
      "text": "and circumstances surrounding the transaction."
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 69433.0,
      "end_time": 74660.0,
      "text": "To have a valid, enforceable contract, you need an agreement,"
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 74660.0,
      "end_time": 78330.0,
      "text": "which consists of an offer and acceptance, consideration,"
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 78330.0,
      "end_time": 83000.0,
      "text": "which is a bargained for exchange of something of value,"
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 83000.0,
      "end_time": 86266.0,
      "text": "contractual capacity, and legality."
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 86266.0,
      "end_time": 89100.0,
      "text": "Legality has to do with purpose of the contract."
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 89100.0,
      "end_time": 91500.0,
      "text": "It has to be legal at the time of execution."
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 93567.0,
      "end_time": 95734.0,
      "text": "There are a couple defenses up front to enforceability"
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 95734.0,
      "end_time": 98366.0,
      "text": "of a contract, voluntary consent--"
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 98367.0,
      "end_time": 101000.0,
      "text": "in other words, a person shouldn&#39;t be forced"
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 101000.0,
      "end_time": 105633.0,
      "text": "to enter into the contract-- as well as the form."
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 105633.0,
      "end_time": 107467.0,
      "text": "Some contracts have to be in writing"
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 107467.0,
      "end_time": 108967.0,
      "text": "under the Statute of Frauds,"
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 108967.0,
      "end_time": 112800.0,
      "text": "which we&#39;ll talk about more later on."
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 112800.0,
      "end_time": 115600.0,
      "text": "There are different types of contracts."
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 115600.0,
      "end_time": 120433.0,
      "text": "A bilateral contract is a promise for a promise."
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 120433.0,
      "end_time": 123700.0,
      "text": "The only thing that the offeree has to do to form the contract"
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 123700.0,
      "end_time": 126667.0,
      "text": "is to make a promise to perform."
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 126667.0,
      "end_time": 129300.0,
      "text": "And a unilateral contract,"
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 129300.00000000001,
      "end_time": 132800.0,
      "text": "the only way the offeree can accept the offer"
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 132800.0,
      "end_time": 139934.0,
      "text": "is by doing the act that was requested in the offer."
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 139934.0,
      "end_time": 142333.0,
      "text": "In other words, a unilateral contract is a promise"
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 142333.0,
      "end_time": 144333.0,
      "text": "for an act."
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 148800.0,
      "end_time": 150400.0,
      "text": "Formal versus informal contracts--"
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 150400.0,
      "end_time": 152266.0,
      "text": "a formal contract is a contract"
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 152266.0,
      "end_time": 155632.0,
      "text": "that has to be in writing to be enforceable."
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 155633.0,
      "end_time": 161867.0,
      "text": "All other contracts are informal."
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 161867.0,
      "end_time": 163330.0,
      "text": "Express versus implied--"
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 163330.0,
      "end_time": 165500.0,
      "text": "\"express\" means expressed in words,"
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 165500.0,
      "end_time": 167500.0,
      "text": "orally or written."
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 167500.0,
      "end_time": 170367.0,
      "text": "And \"implied\" means circumstances"
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 170367.0,
      "end_time": 172000.0,
      "text": "imply that there&#39;s a contract."
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 172000.0,
      "end_time": 174834.0,
      "text": "Basically, requirements are that the plaintiff"
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 174834.0,
      "end_time": 177467.0,
      "text": "furnished goods or services expected to be paid,"
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 177467.0,
      "end_time": 179667.0,
      "text": "and the defendant had a chance to reject"
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 179667.0,
      "end_time": 181767.0,
      "text": "those goods or services but didn&#39;t."
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 184767.0,
      "end_time": 187166.0,
      "text": "Executed verses executory contracts--"
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 187166.0,
      "end_time": 189233.0,
      "text": "an executed contract is where all the parties"
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 189233.0,
      "end_time": 191233.0,
      "text": "have done everything they&#39;re supposed to."
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 191233.0,
      "end_time": 195266.0,
      "text": "An executory contract, at least one of the parties"
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 195266.0,
      "end_time": 196899.0,
      "text": "hasn&#39;t done at least one thing."
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 200433.0,
      "end_time": 205533.0,
      "text": "Talk about the three \"V\"s-- valid, void, and voidable."
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 205533.0,
      "end_time": 210000.0,
      "text": "A valid contract is an agreement, consideration,"
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 210000.0,
      "end_time": 211600.0,
      "text": "contractual capacity, and legality."
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 211600.0,
      "end_time": 214367.0,
      "text": "In other words, a valid contract has all four elements"
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 214367.0,
      "end_time": 215799.0,
      "text": "of a contract."
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 215800.0,
      "end_time": 218333.0,
      "text": "A void contract is really an oxymoron"
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 218333.0,
      "end_time": 221433.0,
      "text": "in that it&#39;s not a contract to start with."
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 221433.0,
      "end_time": 224233.0,
      "text": "And a voidable contract is an unenforceable contract."
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 224233.0,
      "end_time": 227133.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s a contract that&#39;s valid to start with,"
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 227133.0,
      "end_time": 232100.0,
      "text": "but one or both of the parties could back out of it."
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 232100.0,
      "end_time": 236100.0,
      "text": "Basically, an example that would be a valid contract"
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 236100.0,
      "end_time": 237567.0,
      "text": "that a minor enters into is,"
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 237567.0,
      "end_time": 239767.0,
      "text": "so therefore the minor could avoid it,"
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 239767.0,
      "end_time": 241834.0,
      "text": "or that would be a voidable contract."
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 244266.0,
      "end_time": 247899.0,
      "text": "Quasi contract are contracts implied in law"
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 247900.0,
      "end_time": 249166.0,
      "text": "is that you&#39;re gonna see this one"
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 249166.0,
      "end_time": 252367.0,
      "text": "when there is no actual contract."
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 252367.0,
      "end_time": 253566.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s an equitable remedy,"
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 253567.0,
      "end_time": 256660.0,
      "text": "which we&#39;ve talked about earlier in the semester."
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 256649.99999999997,
      "end_time": 259665.99999999997,
      "text": "It&#39;s designed to prevent unjust enrichment"
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 259666.0,
      "end_time": 262633.0,
      "text": "by one of the parties."
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 262633.0,
      "end_time": 266000.0,
      "text": "One example would be if there was a-- not a contract,"
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 266000.0,
      "end_time": 269800.0,
      "text": "but somebody expected to get paid for their services,"
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 269800.0,
      "end_time": 274667.0,
      "text": "then they would get compensated in quantum meruit."
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 274667.0,
      "end_time": 277320.0,
      "text": "In other words, they&#39;d get the reasonable value"
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 277330.0,
      "end_time": 282834.0,
      "text": "of their services."
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 282834.0,
      "end_time": 285100.0,
      "text": "There are limitations."
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 285100.0,
      "end_time": 288934.0,
      "text": "For example, if the other party was enriched,"
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 288934.0,
      "end_time": 297834.0,
      "text": "but it was, for some unnecessary reason-- neglect, misconduct--"
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 297834.0,
      "end_time": 305200.0,
      "text": "for example, if I provided something to another party"
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 305200.0,
      "end_time": 306366.0,
      "text": "that they didn&#39;t ask for,"
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 306367.0,
      "end_time": 308867.0,
      "text": "and they didn&#39;t have an opportunity to reject,"
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 308867.0,
      "end_time": 311300.0,
      "text": "that would mean they necessarily are forced to pay for it."
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 317166.0,
      "end_time": 320567.0,
      "text": "Let&#39;s focus in on the element of agreement."
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 320567.0,
      "end_time": 323633.0,
      "text": "As we said earlier, that&#39;s offer and acceptance."
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 323633.0,
      "end_time": 326866.0,
      "text": "The requirements for an offer are a serious intent,"
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 326867.0,
      "end_time": 330533.0,
      "text": "definiteness, and a communication of the offer"
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 330533.0,
      "end_time": 334800.0,
      "text": "from the offeror to the offeree."
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 334800.0,
      "end_time": 338233.0,
      "text": "In terms of intent, a contract is judged by"
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 338233.0,
      "end_time": 340266.0,
      "text": "what a reasonable person in the offeree&#39;s position"
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 340266.0,
      "end_time": 342330.0,
      "text": "would conclude about the offer."
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 345700.0,
      "end_time": 347700.0,
      "text": "And here are some things that are not offers--"
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 347700.0,
      "end_time": 350000.0,
      "text": "expressions of opinion,"
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 350000.0,
      "end_time": 352934.0,
      "text": "statement of some future intent to enter into a contract"
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 352934.0,
      "end_time": 354900.0,
      "text": "is not an offer,"
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 354900.0,
      "end_time": 358660.0,
      "text": "preliminary negotiations or invitations to negotiate,"
    },
    {
      "index": 112,
      "start_time": 358660.0,
      "end_time": 359200.0,
      "text": "and advertisements."
    },
    {
      "index": 113,
      "start_time": 359200.0,
      "end_time": 362533.0,
      "text": "Typically, you know, for example if I advertise to sell my truck,"
    },
    {
      "index": 114,
      "start_time": 362533.0,
      "end_time": 363900.0,
      "text": "and a hundred people responded,"
    },
    {
      "index": 115,
      "start_time": 363900.0,
      "end_time": 368990.0,
      "text": "I wouldn&#39;t be bound to sell it to all of them."
    },
    {
      "index": 116,
      "start_time": 368100.0,
      "end_time": 371000.0,
      "text": "It would be an invitation for them to negotiate."
    },
    {
      "index": 117,
      "start_time": 379633.0,
      "end_time": 383967.0,
      "text": "An agreement to agree can, under the modern view,"
    },
    {
      "index": 118,
      "start_time": 383967.0,
      "end_time": 388633.0,
      "text": "be enforceable if the parties intended to be bound."
    },
    {
      "index": 119,
      "start_time": 388633.0,
      "end_time": 391332.0,
      "text": "A preliminary agreement can be binding if the parties"
    },
    {
      "index": 120,
      "start_time": 391333.0,
      "end_time": 393500.0,
      "text": "had agreed upon all the essential terms."
    },
    {
      "index": 121,
      "start_time": 396500.0,
      "end_time": 399000.0,
      "text": "The offer has to be definite."
    },
    {
      "index": 122,
      "start_time": 399000.0,
      "end_time": 401867.0,
      "text": "The terms expressed or implied need to identify the party,"
    },
    {
      "index": 123,
      "start_time": 401867.0,
      "end_time": 406333.0,
      "text": "the object or the contract, consideration to be paid,"
    },
    {
      "index": 124,
      "start_time": 406333.0,
      "end_time": 413000.0,
      "text": "and things like the time of payment, delivery, performance."
    },
    {
      "index": 125,
      "start_time": 413000.0,
      "end_time": 415600.0,
      "text": "An offer can require specific terms"
    },
    {
      "index": 126,
      "start_time": 415600.0,
      "end_time": 417433.0,
      "text": "to make the contract definite,"
    },
    {
      "index": 127,
      "start_time": 417433.0,
      "end_time": 420166.0,
      "text": "and a court can supply missing terms if the parties intend"
    },
    {
      "index": 128,
      "start_time": 420166.0,
      "end_time": 424660.0,
      "text": "to form a contract."
    },
    {
      "index": 129,
      "start_time": 424660.0,
      "end_time": 428133.0,
      "text": "The offer needs to be communicated to the offeree."
    },
    {
      "index": 130,
      "start_time": 428133.0,
      "end_time": 430799.0,
      "text": "The offeree&#39;s knowledge of the offer can be either direct"
    },
    {
      "index": 131,
      "start_time": 430800.0,
      "end_time": 432800.0,
      "text": "or through an agent."
    },
    {
      "index": 132,
      "start_time": 434567.0,
      "end_time": 438367.0,
      "text": "And an offer is terminated by the actions of the parties"
    },
    {
      "index": 133,
      "start_time": 438367.0,
      "end_time": 440400.0,
      "text": "or by operation of law."
    },
    {
      "index": 134,
      "start_time": 443200.0,
      "end_time": 450400.0,
      "text": "One of the things the offeror could do is revoke the offer."
    },
    {
      "index": 135,
      "start_time": 450400.0,
      "end_time": 452400.0,
      "text": "And the offer can be withdrawn any time"
    },
    {
      "index": 136,
      "start_time": 452400.0,
      "end_time": 458299.0,
      "text": "prior to the acceptance, unless it&#39;s irrevocable."
    },
    {
      "index": 137,
      "start_time": 458300.0,
      "end_time": 461100.0,
      "text": "And typically, the offer is effective when the offeree"
    },
    {
      "index": 138,
      "start_time": 461100.0,
      "end_time": 463100.0,
      "text": "or the offeree&#39;s agent receives it."
    },
    {
      "index": 139,
      "start_time": 467166.0,
      "end_time": 469767.0,
      "text": "More on termination by action of the offeree."
    },
    {
      "index": 140,
      "start_time": 469767.0,
      "end_time": 473433.0,
      "text": "The offeree could reject the offer."
    },
    {
      "index": 141,
      "start_time": 473433.0,
      "end_time": 475433.0,
      "text": "That would be either expressed or implied."
    },
    {
      "index": 142,
      "start_time": 479133.0,
      "end_time": 483133.0,
      "text": "The offer could be terminated by a rejection counter-offer."
    },
    {
      "index": 143,
      "start_time": 483133.0,
      "end_time": 485299.0,
      "text": "So if somebody offered to sell you something for $100,"
    },
    {
      "index": 144,
      "start_time": 485300.0,
      "end_time": 488800.0,
      "text": "and you responded, \"I wouldn&#39;t pay more than 50,\""
    },
    {
      "index": 145,
      "start_time": 488800.0,
      "end_time": 493800.0,
      "text": "that would be a rejection and potentially a counter-offer."
    },
    {
      "index": 146,
      "start_time": 493800.0,
      "end_time": 497367.0,
      "text": "Mirror Image Rule says, under common law,"
    },
    {
      "index": 147,
      "start_time": 497367.0,
      "end_time": 500660.0,
      "text": "any change in the terms automatically terminates the offer."
    },
    {
      "index": 148,
      "start_time": 500660.0,
      "end_time": 507232.0,
      "text": "So if I were to accept with different terms,"
    },
    {
      "index": 149,
      "start_time": 507233.0,
      "end_time": 512633.0,
      "text": "that wouldn&#39;t be a contract."
    },
    {
      "index": 150,
      "start_time": 512633.00000000006,
      "end_time": 514734.00000000006,
      "text": "The offer could be terminated by operation of law"
    },
    {
      "index": 151,
      "start_time": 514734.00000000006,
      "end_time": 516467.00000000006,
      "text": "through lapse of time."
    },
    {
      "index": 152,
      "start_time": 516467.0,
      "end_time": 520660.0,
      "text": "The offer might be open for a specific period of time."
    },
    {
      "index": 153,
      "start_time": 520659.99999999994,
      "end_time": 521232.99999999994,
      "text": "Destruction or death--"
    },
    {
      "index": 154,
      "start_time": 521232.0,
      "end_time": 522532.0,
      "text": "destruction of the subject matter,"
    },
    {
      "index": 155,
      "start_time": 522533.0,
      "end_time": 527467.0,
      "text": "death of the offeror or offeree."
    },
    {
      "index": 156,
      "start_time": 527467.0,
      "end_time": 530867.0,
      "text": "Or even some, what used to be legal,"
    },
    {
      "index": 157,
      "start_time": 530867.0,
      "end_time": 534533.0,
      "text": "now illegal purpose for the contract."
    },
    {
      "index": 158,
      "start_time": 537567.0,
      "end_time": 539800.0,
      "text": "Acceptance is voluntary."
    },
    {
      "index": 159,
      "start_time": 539800.0,
      "end_time": 542000.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s made by the offeree."
    },
    {
      "index": 160,
      "start_time": 542000.0,
      "end_time": 545467.0,
      "text": "It shows their assent or agreement to the contract,"
    },
    {
      "index": 161,
      "start_time": 545467.0,
      "end_time": 547766.0,
      "text": "and specifically the terms of that offer."
    },
    {
      "index": 162,
      "start_time": 547767.0,
      "end_time": 550000.0,
      "text": "This is the Mirror Image Rule,"
    },
    {
      "index": 163,
      "start_time": 550000.0,
      "end_time": 554266.0,
      "text": "that the acceptance mirrors the offer."
    },
    {
      "index": 164,
      "start_time": 554266.0,
      "end_time": 556266.0,
      "text": "Silence can be acceptance."
    },
    {
      "index": 165,
      "start_time": 561867.0,
      "end_time": 567367.0,
      "text": "In some cases, when the offeree has a duty to speak,"
    },
    {
      "index": 166,
      "start_time": 567367.0,
      "end_time": 571900.0,
      "text": "he takes the benefit of services with the opportunity to reject"
    },
    {
      "index": 167,
      "start_time": 571900.0,
      "end_time": 576400.0,
      "text": "and doesn&#39;t, that would be considered an acceptance."
    },
    {
      "index": 168,
      "start_time": 576400.0,
      "end_time": 580333.0,
      "text": "Or that&#39;s the way the parties have done it in the past."
    },
    {
      "index": 169,
      "start_time": 584367.0,
      "end_time": 585500.0,
      "text": "In a bilateral contract,"
    },
    {
      "index": 170,
      "start_time": 585500.0,
      "end_time": 587467.0,
      "text": "communication of the acceptance is necessary"
    },
    {
      "index": 171,
      "start_time": 587467.0,
      "end_time": 590165.0,
      "text": "because of the mutual exchange of promises."
    },
    {
      "index": 172,
      "start_time": 590166.0,
      "end_time": 594734.0,
      "text": "Unilaterally, acceptance is evident, because it&#39;s an action."
    },
    {
      "index": 173,
      "start_time": 594734.0,
      "end_time": 597567.0,
      "text": "You don&#39;t need to notify the other party."
    },
    {
      "index": 174,
      "start_time": 597567.0,
      "end_time": 601133.0,
      "text": "Instead, your notice is your performance of the act."
    },
    {
      "index": 175,
      "start_time": 606667.0,
      "end_time": 608967.0,
      "text": "In bilateral contracts, acceptance is timely."
    },
    {
      "index": 176,
      "start_time": 608967.0,
      "end_time": 610934.0,
      "text": "If it&#39;s made before the offer&#39;s terminated,"
    },
    {
      "index": 177,
      "start_time": 610934.0,
      "end_time": 612467.0,
      "text": "there&#39;s the Mailbox Rule,"
    },
    {
      "index": 178,
      "start_time": 612467.0,
      "end_time": 614699.0,
      "text": "which basically says the acceptance is effective"
    },
    {
      "index": 179,
      "start_time": 614700.0,
      "end_time": 620300.0,
      "text": "upon getting into the mail."
    },
    {
      "index": 180,
      "start_time": 620300.0,
      "end_time": 625300.0,
      "text": "Could be some issues with that, you know, if the other party"
    },
    {
      "index": 181,
      "start_time": 625300.0,
      "end_time": 628867.0,
      "text": "said the acceptance isn&#39;t effective"
    },
    {
      "index": 182,
      "start_time": 628867.0,
      "end_time": 633199.0,
      "text": "until it actually gets to them."
    },
    {
      "index": 183,
      "start_time": 642767.0,
      "end_time": 646633.0,
      "text": "A party could specify how they want acceptance to be made."
    },
    {
      "index": 184,
      "start_time": 650500.0,
      "end_time": 652934.0,
      "text": "And in that case, then it would be an acceptance"
    },
    {
      "index": 185,
      "start_time": 652934.0,
      "end_time": 657934.0,
      "text": "if it wasn&#39;t delivered in a way that was authorized."
    },
    {
      "index": 186,
      "start_time": 663330.0,
      "end_time": 666000.0,
      "text": "Could be online offers."
    },
    {
      "index": 187,
      "start_time": 666000.0,
      "end_time": 669166.0,
      "text": "If there is, then the seller&#39;s web site"
    },
    {
      "index": 188,
      "start_time": 669166.0,
      "end_time": 671667.0,
      "text": "should include a hyperlink"
    },
    {
      "index": 189,
      "start_time": 671667.0,
      "end_time": 675867.0,
      "text": "to the full details of the offer."
    },
    {
      "index": 190,
      "start_time": 675867.0,
      "end_time": 679834.0,
      "text": "Here are some things to include pretty much in any contract,"
    },
    {
      "index": 191,
      "start_time": 679834.0,
      "end_time": 685766.0,
      "text": "but this can be an issue in online contracts as well--"
    },
    {
      "index": 192,
      "start_time": 685767.0,
      "end_time": 689834.0,
      "text": "how the other party would accept payment, return policy,"
    },
    {
      "index": 193,
      "start_time": 689834.0,
      "end_time": 693900.0,
      "text": "a disclaimer concerning the liability,"
    },
    {
      "index": 194,
      "start_time": 693900.0,
      "end_time": 698400.0,
      "text": "a limit on the remedies that the other party can invoke"
    },
    {
      "index": 195,
      "start_time": 698400.0,
      "end_time": 700300.0,
      "text": "if there&#39;s a breach of contract,"
    },
    {
      "index": 196,
      "start_time": 700300.0,
      "end_time": 704599.0,
      "text": "privacy policy, because you potentially are providing"
    },
    {
      "index": 197,
      "start_time": 704600.0,
      "end_time": 707467.0,
      "text": "identifying information over the internet,"
    },
    {
      "index": 198,
      "start_time": 707467.0,
      "end_time": 711699.0,
      "text": "and forum and choice-of-law clauses,"
    },
    {
      "index": 199,
      "start_time": 711700.0,
      "end_time": 713967.0,
      "text": "if there is a dispute where it would be settled"
    },
    {
      "index": 200,
      "start_time": 713967.0,
      "end_time": 718800.0,
      "text": "as well as which law of which particular jurisdiction"
    },
    {
      "index": 201,
      "start_time": 718800.0,
      "end_time": 720567.0,
      "text": "would apply."
    },
    {
      "index": 202,
      "start_time": 722900.0,
      "end_time": 726100.0,
      "text": "Click-on agreements."
    },
    {
      "index": 203,
      "start_time": 726100.0,
      "end_time": 731867.0,
      "text": "There&#39;s a binding contract when a party clicks on a box,"
    },
    {
      "index": 204,
      "start_time": 731867.0,
      "end_time": 734766.0,
      "text": "indicating they accept or agree."
    },
    {
      "index": 205,
      "start_time": 734767.0,
      "end_time": 738266.0,
      "text": "That could be through web site or software."
    },
    {
      "index": 206,
      "start_time": 738266.0,
      "end_time": 740367.0,
      "text": "Law doesn&#39;t require that the party actually read"
    },
    {
      "index": 207,
      "start_time": 740367.0,
      "end_time": 743132.0,
      "text": "all of the terms, just that they had access to the terms."
    },
    {
      "index": 208,
      "start_time": 743133.0,
      "end_time": 746600.0,
      "text": "Courts generally enforce click-on agreements,"
    },
    {
      "index": 209,
      "start_time": 746600.0,
      "end_time": 749367.0,
      "text": "as well as shrink-wrap agreements."
    },
    {
      "index": 210,
      "start_time": 749367.0,
      "end_time": 754900.0,
      "text": "So you could have software inside of a box, sealed up,"
    },
    {
      "index": 211,
      "start_time": 754900.0,
      "end_time": 757567.0,
      "text": "and the parties agree, by opening the box"
    },
    {
      "index": 212,
      "start_time": 757567.0,
      "end_time": 760867.0,
      "text": "or installing the software, to the terms."
    },
    {
      "index": 213,
      "start_time": 760867.0,
      "end_time": 763934.0,
      "text": "Basically they don&#39;t necessarily see the terms"
    },
    {
      "index": 214,
      "start_time": 763934.0,
      "end_time": 766500.0,
      "text": "in shrink-wrap agreement until afterwards."
    },
    {
      "index": 215,
      "start_time": 766500.0,
      "end_time": 769533.0,
      "text": "And the court reasons that they still would have an opportunity"
    },
    {
      "index": 216,
      "start_time": 769533.0,
      "end_time": 773467.0,
      "text": "to reject it if they see the terms."
    },
    {
      "index": 217,
      "start_time": 773467.0,
      "end_time": 777400.0,
      "text": "Browse-wrap terms."
    },
    {
      "index": 218,
      "start_time": 777400.0,
      "end_time": 779834.0,
      "text": "It says, \"Unlike click-on agreements,"
    },
    {
      "index": 219,
      "start_time": 779834.0,
      "end_time": 782766.0,
      "text": "\"browse wrap-terms do not require assent"
    },
    {
      "index": 220,
      "start_time": 782767.0,
      "end_time": 783900.0,
      "text": "\"and are usually unenforceable.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 221,
      "start_time": 783900.0,
      "end_time": 787233.0,
      "text": "What that means is that these are over the internet,"
    },
    {
      "index": 222,
      "start_time": 787233.0,
      "end_time": 790233.0,
      "text": "and somebody would agree to terms,"
    },
    {
      "index": 223,
      "start_time": 790233.0,
      "end_time": 792467.0,
      "text": "and if it&#39;s not possible for them to see"
    },
    {
      "index": 224,
      "start_time": 792467.0,
      "end_time": 796867.0,
      "text": "what the terms their agreement is about beforehand,"
    },
    {
      "index": 225,
      "start_time": 796867.0,
      "end_time": 800599.0,
      "text": "then the court typically doesn&#39;t enforce that."
    },
    {
      "index": 226,
      "start_time": 803400.0,
      "end_time": 806266.0,
      "text": "There&#39;s the E-SIGN law back in 2000,"
    },
    {
      "index": 227,
      "start_time": 806266.0,
      "end_time": 810000.0,
      "text": "it gives e-signatures and e-documents legal force."
    },
    {
      "index": 228,
      "start_time": 810000.0,
      "end_time": 813433.0,
      "text": "So you can have documents that are electronic"
    },
    {
      "index": 229,
      "start_time": 813433.0,
      "end_time": 817934.0,
      "text": "that would be the same as paper in terms of enforceability."
    },
    {
      "index": 230,
      "start_time": 817934.0,
      "end_time": 819433.0,
      "text": "For an e-signature to be enforceable,"
    },
    {
      "index": 231,
      "start_time": 819433.0,
      "end_time": 823667.0,
      "text": "the contracting parties must have agreed to use e-signatures."
    },
    {
      "index": 232,
      "start_time": 823667.0,
      "end_time": 825767.0,
      "text": "And it doesn&#39;t apply to all documents."
    },
    {
      "index": 233,
      "start_time": 830266.0,
      "end_time": 834533.0,
      "text": "UETA-- \"Uniform Electronic Transaction Act\"--"
    },
    {
      "index": 234,
      "start_time": 834533.0,
      "end_time": 836533.0,
      "text": "is it purposes to remove barriers"
    },
    {
      "index": 235,
      "start_time": 836533.0,
      "end_time": 837667.0,
      "text": "to forming electronic commerce,"
    },
    {
      "index": 236,
      "start_time": 837667.0,
      "end_time": 840834.0,
      "text": "not create new types of contracts."
    },
    {
      "index": 237,
      "start_time": 840834.0,
      "end_time": 843333.0,
      "text": "And an e-signature could be anything"
    },
    {
      "index": 238,
      "start_time": 843333.0,
      "end_time": 845266.0,
      "text": "from electric sound symbol,"
    },
    {
      "index": 239,
      "start_time": 845266.0,
      "end_time": 848967.0,
      "text": "process associated with a record."
    },
    {
      "index": 240,
      "start_time": 848967.0,
      "end_time": 851600.0,
      "text": "And a record is information that&#39;s inscribed"
    },
    {
      "index": 241,
      "start_time": 851600.0,
      "end_time": 854433.0,
      "text": "on a tangible medium or stored in electronic"
    },
    {
      "index": 242,
      "start_time": 854433.0,
      "end_time": 858233.0,
      "text": "or other medium that is retrievable in visual form."
    },
    {
      "index": 243,
      "start_time": 860800.0,
      "end_time": 863990.0,
      "text": "UETA doesn&#39;t create new rules,"
    },
    {
      "index": 244,
      "start_time": 863100.0,
      "end_time": 867400.0,
      "text": "but rather enforces real world rules on electronic contracts."
    },
    {
      "index": 245,
      "start_time": 867400.0,
      "end_time": 869500.0,
      "text": "It only applies to e-records and e-signatures"
    },
    {
      "index": 246,
      "start_time": 869500.0,
      "end_time": 871767.0,
      "text": "related to a transaction."
    },
    {
      "index": 247,
      "start_time": 871767.0,
      "end_time": 875467.0,
      "text": "It doesn&#39;t apply to wills or testamentary trusts."
    },
    {
      "index": 248,
      "start_time": 875467.0,
      "end_time": 877800.0,
      "text": "And it doesn&#39;t apply unless each party has previously agreed"
    },
    {
      "index": 249,
      "start_time": 877800.0,
      "end_time": 880333.0,
      "text": "to conduct electronic transactions."
    },
    {
      "index": 250,
      "start_time": 880333.0,
      "end_time": 883733.0,
      "text": "But that could be implied by the conduct"
    },
    {
      "index": 251,
      "start_time": 883734.0,
      "end_time": 885734.0,
      "text": "of the parties or prior dealings."
    },
    {
      "index": 252,
      "start_time": 889533.0,
      "end_time": 891834.0,
      "text": "E-SIGN explicitly refers to UETA and provides"
    },
    {
      "index": 253,
      "start_time": 891834.0,
      "end_time": 896500.0,
      "text": "that E-SIGN is preempted by state passing of UETA,"
    },
    {
      "index": 254,
      "start_time": 896500.0,
      "end_time": 900300.0,
      "text": "but the state law must conform to minimum of E-SIGN procedures."
    },
    {
      "index": 255,
      "start_time": 902633.0,
      "end_time": 906367.0,
      "text": "Looking at consideration, a second element."
    },
    {
      "index": 256,
      "start_time": 906367.0,
      "end_time": 909733.0,
      "text": "It must be something of legally sufficient value."
    },
    {
      "index": 257,
      "start_time": 909734.0,
      "end_time": 911667.0,
      "text": "It could be a promise, performance,"
    },
    {
      "index": 258,
      "start_time": 911667.0,
      "end_time": 914934.0,
      "text": "or promise to forbear, not do something."
    },
    {
      "index": 259,
      "start_time": 914934.0,
      "end_time": 918650.0,
      "text": "It has to be bargained-for-exchange."
    },
    {
      "index": 260,
      "start_time": 918660.0,
      "end_time": 920660.0,
      "text": "It provides the basis for the bargain,"
    },
    {
      "index": 261,
      "start_time": 920660.0,
      "end_time": 922800.0,
      "text": "something that has legal value."
    },
    {
      "index": 262,
      "start_time": 922800.0,
      "end_time": 928300.0,
      "text": "As we mentioned, that promise has to be legally detrimental"
    },
    {
      "index": 263,
      "start_time": 928300.0,
      "end_time": 933666.0,
      "text": "to the promisee or legally beneficial to the promisor."
    },
    {
      "index": 264,
      "start_time": 933667.0,
      "end_time": 935867.0,
      "text": "Court typically doesn&#39;t get involved in the adequacy"
    },
    {
      "index": 265,
      "start_time": 935867.0,
      "end_time": 938967.0,
      "text": "or the amount of the consideration."
    },
    {
      "index": 266,
      "start_time": 938967.0,
      "end_time": 943000.0,
      "text": "It doesn&#39;t really protect people who enter into unwise contracts,"
    },
    {
      "index": 267,
      "start_time": 943000.0,
      "end_time": 944967.0,
      "text": "pay too much for something,"
    },
    {
      "index": 268,
      "start_time": 944967.0,
      "end_time": 950900.0,
      "text": "unless they determine that it&#39;s shockingly inadequate."
    },
    {
      "index": 269,
      "start_time": 950900.0,
      "end_time": 952834.0,
      "text": "This would be called \"unconscionability.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 270,
      "start_time": 955834.0,
      "end_time": 960199.0,
      "text": "Sometimes, something sounds like consideration but not really."
    },
    {
      "index": 271,
      "start_time": 960200.0,
      "end_time": 962400.0,
      "text": "If somebody had a preexisting duty to do something,"
    },
    {
      "index": 272,
      "start_time": 962400.0,
      "end_time": 965600.0,
      "text": "they can&#39;t promise to do it again for more consideration."
    },
    {
      "index": 273,
      "start_time": 968266.0,
      "end_time": 969733.0,
      "text": "There are some exceptions to that."
    },
    {
      "index": 274,
      "start_time": 969734.0,
      "end_time": 972600.0,
      "text": "Past consideration-- if it was done for something"
    },
    {
      "index": 275,
      "start_time": 972600.0,
      "end_time": 977330.0,
      "text": "that was already paid for."
    },
    {
      "index": 276,
      "start_time": 977330.0,
      "end_time": 980934.0,
      "text": "An illusory promise-- it sounds like a promise."
    },
    {
      "index": 277,
      "start_time": 980934.0,
      "end_time": 982934.0,
      "text": "You know, \"I promise to make a promise in the future.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 278,
      "start_time": 982934.0,
      "end_time": 986733.0,
      "text": "It uses the word \"promise\" but it&#39;s really illusory."
    },
    {
      "index": 279,
      "start_time": 989800.0,
      "end_time": 991132.0,
      "text": "It could be settlement of claims."
    },
    {
      "index": 280,
      "start_time": 991133.0,
      "end_time": 994500.0,
      "text": "Accord and satisfaction is when you&#39;ve got a creditor--"
    },
    {
      "index": 281,
      "start_time": 994500.0,
      "end_time": 996400.0,
      "text": "debtor, typically--"
    },
    {
      "index": 282,
      "start_time": 996400.0,
      "end_time": 1000934.0,
      "text": "and the creditor agrees to accept something different"
    },
    {
      "index": 283,
      "start_time": 1000930.0,
      "end_time": 1003429.0,
      "text": "than the debtor originally promised to pay"
    },
    {
      "index": 284,
      "start_time": 1003430.0,
      "end_time": 1006263.0,
      "text": "to discharge the debt."
    },
    {
      "index": 285,
      "start_time": 1006270.0,
      "end_time": 1009994.0,
      "text": "Could be a release, covenant not to sue."
    },
    {
      "index": 286,
      "start_time": 1011730.0,
      "end_time": 1013326.0,
      "text": "And then promissory estoppel--"
    },
    {
      "index": 287,
      "start_time": 1013330.0,
      "end_time": 1017767.0,
      "text": "probably one of the hardest concepts in the chapter."
    },
    {
      "index": 288,
      "start_time": 1017770.0,
      "end_time": 1019403.0,
      "text": "When somebody makes a promise,"
    },
    {
      "index": 289,
      "start_time": 1019400.0,
      "end_time": 1024333.0,
      "text": "and the other party relies, to their detriment--"
    },
    {
      "index": 290,
      "start_time": 1024329.9999999999,
      "end_time": 1029796.9999999999,
      "text": "and justifiably relies-- and that reliance is substantial,"
    },
    {
      "index": 291,
      "start_time": 1029800.0,
      "end_time": 1032834.0,
      "text": "then the court would enforce that."
    },
    {
      "index": 292,
      "start_time": 1032829.9999999999,
      "end_time": 1036462.9999999999,
      "text": "Even in situations where the parties don&#39;t have a contract."
    },
    {
      "index": 293,
      "start_time": 1036470.0,
      "end_time": 1040303.0,
      "text": "So that&#39;s the end of chapter 7."
    }
  ]
}